==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*[[OK]], ok, okay, okey, okie (''okie-dokie'')

===Usage===
The interjection '''OK''' is probably the most used term in the world, and it exists with the same meaning in most of the major world languages

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-okay.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''okay'''
#[[endorsement]]; [[approval]]
#:''We can start as soon as we get the '''okay'''.''

====Translations====
*Estonian: [[OK]], [[olgu]]
*Finnish: [[OK]]

===Adjective===
'''okay'''
#[[all right]]; [[acceptable]]; [[satisfactory]]
#:''Do you think it's '''okay''' to stay here for the night?''
#[[good]]; good enough
#:''The soup was '''okay''', but the dessert was excellent.''
#[[all right]]; in good [[health]] or emotional [[condition]]
#:''He's not feeling well now, but he should be '''okay''' after some rest.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[hyvä]]

===Adverb===
'''okay'''
#[[satisfactorily]], [[well]]
#:''The team did '''okay''' in the playoffs.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[hyvin]]

===Interjection===
'''okay'''
#used to introduce an example or approximation; [[all right]]
#:''Okay, I'm thinking of a number...''

===Verb===
'''to okay'''
#to [[approve]]
#:''I don't want to '''okay''' this amount of money.''

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[hyväksyä]]

